identity.name: ContactPointSystem
identity.description: Contact point system enumerator. All codes from system http://hl7.org/fhir/contact-point-system.

identity.name: Code
identity.description: The code (used as the code in the resource instance). If the code is in italics, this indicates that the code is not selectable ('Abstract')

identity.name: Display
identity.description: The display (used in the display element of a Coding). If there is no display, implementers should not simply display the code, but map the concept into their application

identity.name: Definition
identity.description: An explanation of the meaning of the concept

values: The value is a telephone number used for voice calls. Use of full international numbers starting with + is recommended to enable automatic dialing support but not required.
The value is a fax machine. Use of full international numbers starting with + is recommended to enable automatic dialing support but not required.
The value is an email address.
The value is a pager number. These may be local pager numbers that are only usable on a particular pager system.

A contact that is not a phone, fax, pager or email address and is expressed as a URL. This is intended for various personal contacts including blogs, Skype, Twitter, Facebook, etc. Do not use for email addresses.

A contact that can be used for sending an sms message (e.g. mobile phones, some landlines)
other

A contact that is not a phone, fax, page or email address and is not expressible as a URL. E.g. Internal mail address. This SHOULD NOT be used for contacts that are expressible as a URL (e.g. Skype, Twitter, Facebook, etc.) Extensions may be used to distinguish "other" contact types.
